description:
In this kata, you will be escaping a prison using a bomb. However, the compiler will not let you throw this bomb:
```java
final class Bomb extends Exception {
  public Bomb() {
    this(checkCreateBomb());
  }

  private Bomb(Void unused) {
    checkCreateBomb();
  }

  private static Void checkCreateBomb() {
    System.getSecurityManager().checkPermission(new RuntimePermission("createBomb"));
    return null;
  }
}
```

Also, the prison guard keeps you from creating bombs:
```java
final class PrisonGuard extends SecurityManager {
  @Override
  public void checkPermission(Permission perm) {
    String name = perm.getName();
    if (name.equals("createBomb") || name.equals("setSecurityManager"))
      throw new SecurityException();
  }
}
```

To pass this kata, you will need to throw an instance of `Bomb`.
